pr_review_comment_body:
@rcrowder How about move `using namespace` directives into between the `includes` and the class. Something like this:

```
#include <nupic/math/SparseBinaryMatrix.hpp>
#include <nupic/proto/SparseBinaryMatrixProto.capnp.h>
#include <nupic/types/Types.h>

using namespace capnp;

namespace nupic
{
```

@carmstrong 

> again, I think having controller ensure the log directory exists on startup is the way to go here

As far as I can tell (and I've double-checked this a few times) it already works that way.  Sanity check for me... have you seen it behave to the contrary?

I think the right signature is 

    def with_columns(self, *labels_and_values, *, formatter=None)

and it's limited to giving the same formatter to every new column or no formatter at all.
